main event: A reddish-white object moving very slowly in a zigzag course was observed in the sky near San Diego, California on April 6, 1950.
interesting points: The object moved at a low altitude and disappeared to the north.
The witness could not identify the object as a reflection, meteor, or small aircraft.
The object moved too slowly to be a meteor and did not have the characteristics of an aircraft.
The report suggests the object may have been a mirage or weather reflection, but the nature of the sighting remains unknown.
The report indicates that an investigation could not be conducted due to a lack of witnesses or physical evidence.
